# Photogram API

Photogram is a fictional clone of Instagram. Users can post photos and share with their family and friends as well as 'like' and 'follow' other users.

## User Registration [/api/users/register]

### Register a new User [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "firstname": 'John',
            "lastname": 'Doe',
            "username": "jdoe",
            "password": "password123",
            "email": "jdoe@example.com",
            "location": "Kingston, Jamaica",
            "biography": "A short bio about me",
            "profile_photo": "profile-photo.jpg"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "message": "User successfully registered"
        }
        

## User Login [/api/user/login]

### Login an existing User [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "username": "jdoe",
            "password": "password123"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.XbPfbIHMI6arZ3Y922BhjWgQzWXcXNrz0ogtVhfEd2o"
            "message": "User successfully logged in."
        }
        
